    "problemStatement": "The Chef is given a sequence of **N** integers **A1,  A2, ..., AN**. He has to process **Q** queries on the above sequence. Each query is represented by three integers:\n\n\n\n**L R K** =&gt; report cardinality of **{ i : K** divides **Ai**, **L** ≤ **i** ≤ **R }**. In other words, how many integers in the subsequence starting at **L**th element and ending at **R**th element are divisible by **K**.",
    "constraints": [
      "**1** ≤ **N, Q ** ≤ **100000 (105)**",
      "**1** ≤ **Ai ** ≤ **100000 (105)**",
      "**1** ≤ **L** ≤ **R** ≤ **N**",
      "**1** ≤ **K ** ≤ **100000 (105)**",
      "&nbsp;",
      "Example**Input:**",
      "8 5",
      "3 5 1 4 6 9 12 6",
      "3 6 2",
      "3 6 4",
      "4 8 3",
      "2 6 7",
      "8 8 6",
      "**Output:**",
      "2",
      "1",
      "4",
      "0",
      "1"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "**N****Q****N****A1,  A2, ..., AN****Q****L R K**&nbsp;",
    "outputFormat": "",
